The paper deals with visual recognition and natural language processing, which are both core topics in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of compressive sensing (CS) is a key aspect of the paper, which suggests that it could also be relevant to information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper involves deep neural networks, which are a common tool in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM) research.
